---
import "../../styles/global.css";
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About — MCZ">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16 text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg2">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-[32px] font-normal text-fg mb-8">About MCZ</h1>

    <p class="mb-4">MCZ is an open-source binary container format designed for streaming sequential images — like manga chapters, webtoons, or any image gallery — over HTTP with minimal latency.</p>

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-fg mt-8 mb-3">Why MCZ exists</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">Traditional formats like ZIP/CBZ put their index at the end of the file, requiring a full download before any content can be displayed. PDF scatters its cross-reference table. MCZ puts the index at byte 0, so dimensions are available instantly and pages stream progressively as data arrives.</p>

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-fg mt-8 mb-3">Who built this</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">MCZ is created and maintained by <a href="https://github.com/nghyane" class="text-accent underline hover:no-underline">nghyane</a>. It's built with Rust for the CLI/library and TypeScript for the browser runtime.</p>

    <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-fg mt-8 mb-3">Open source</h2>
    <p>MCZ is MIT-licensed. The format specification, CLI tool, JS library, and this website are all open source on <a href="https://github.com/nghyane/mcz" class="text-accent underline hover:no-underline">GitHub</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
